*   ^ This article always assumes `ψ` is normalized to 1. If it’s not, you just divide by its norm, `||ψ||`, in all formulas. It’s basic hygiene.
*   ^ This assumes the eigenvalues are not degenerate. If they are, things get a bit more complicated, but the core idea remains.

